#: ../../PyMOTW/os/index.rst:401
msgid ""
"The library documentation for :func:`access()` includes two special "
"warnings. First, there isn't much sense in calling :func:`access()` to test "
"whether a file can be opened before actually calling :func:`open()` on it. "
"There is a small, but real, window of time between the two calls during "
"which the permissions on the file could change. The other warning applies "
"mostly to networked filesystems that extend the POSIX permission semantics. "
"Some filesystem types may respond to the POSIX call that a process has "
"permission to access a file, then report a failure when the attempt is made "
"using :func:`open()` for some reason not tested via the POSIX call. All in "
"all, it is better to call :func:`open()` with the required mode and catch "
"the :ref:`IOError <exceptions-IOError>` raised if there is a problem."
